# DedgeAuth Ecosystem Architecture

**Mandatory read:** `docs/DedgeAuth-Ecosystem-Architecture.md` contains the full architecture reference with Mermaid diagrams for auth flow, build pipeline, IIS deployment, and all interconnections. Consult it before making changes that affect multiple apps.

## IIS Topology

All apps run as virtual applications under `Default Web Site` on port 80:

| Virtual Path | App Pool | DotNetDll | ApiPort | Health |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `/` | DefaultWebSite | (static redirect) | — | — |
| `/DedgeAuth` | DedgeAuth | `DedgeAuth.Api.dll` | 8100 | `/health` |
| `/DocView` | DocView | `DocView.dll` | 8282 | — |
| `/GenericLogHandler` | GenericLogHandler | `GenericLogHandler.WebApi.dll` | 8110 | `/health` |
| `/ServerMonitorDashboard` | ServerMonitorDashboard | `ServerMonitorDashboard.dll` | 8998 | `/api/IsAlive` |
| `/AutoDocJson` | AutoDocJson | `AutoDocJson.Web.dll` | 5280 | `/health` |
| `/AutoDoc` | AutoDoc | (static HTML) | — | — |

## Auth Flow (auth code exchange)

1. User visits consumer app → `DedgeAuthRedirectMiddleware` redirects to `/DedgeAuth/login.html?returnUrl=...`
2. User logs in → DedgeAuth returns JWT + short-lived auth code
3. DedgeAuth redirects back to consumer app with `?code=<authCode>`
4. `DedgeAuthTokenExtractionMiddleware` exchanges code server-to-server via `POST /api/auth/exchange`
5. JWT stored in `DedgeAuth_access_token` cookie, browser redirected to clean URL
6. `DedgeAuthSessionValidationMiddleware` validates session via `GET /api/auth/validate` (cached 30s)
7. On cache miss, fires-and-forgets `POST /api/visits/record` to record the visit

## Middleware Pipeline (consumer apps)

```
DedgeAuthTokenExtractionMiddleware  → extracts ?code= or ?token= or cookie → sets Authorization header
UseAuthentication                → JWT validation
UseAuthorization                 → policy evaluation
DedgeAuthSessionValidationMiddleware → validates with DedgeAuth server, records visits
DedgeAuthRedirectMiddleware         → redirects unauthenticated to login
```

All registered by `app.UseDedgeAuth()`. Do NOT call `UseAuthentication()`/`UseAuthorization()` separately.

## UI Asset Proxy

Consumer HTML uses **relative paths** (no leading `/`) to load DedgeAuth assets through `MapDedgeAuthProxy()`:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="api/DedgeAuth/ui/common.css">
<style id="DedgeAuth-tenant-css"></style>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.css">
<div id="DedgeAuthUserMenu"></div>
<script src="api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.js"></script>
```

`DedgeAuth-user.js` is served from DedgeAuth server — changes propagate to all apps without rebuild. It handles: user menu, app switcher, tenant CSS/logo/favicon injection, visit tracking link.

## Build Commands

```powershell
# Build ALL (DedgeAuth first, then all consumer apps referencing DedgeAuth.Client)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1"

# Build individual apps
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\Build-And-Publish.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DocView\Build-And-Publish.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\GenericLogHandler\Build-And-Publish.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\Build-And-Publish.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\AutoDocJson\Build-And-Publish.ps1"
```

## IIS Deploy Commands

```powershell
# Redeploy all (teardown + iisreset + rebuild from templates)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"

# Deploy single app
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-DeployApp.ps1" -SiteName DedgeAuth

# Uninstall single app
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-UninstallApp.ps1" -SiteName DedgeAuth

# Diagnose broken app
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\Test-IISSite.ps1" -SiteName DedgeAuth
```

## Deploy templates location

`C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\templates\` — naming: `<SiteName>_<InstallSource>.deploy.json`

## Database (PostgreSQL)

Server: `t-no1fkxtst-db:8432` | Database: `DedgeAuth`

Key tables: `users`, `apps`, `app_permissions`, `tenants` (CSS, logo, icon, app routing), `user_visits`, `login_tokens`, `refresh_tokens`

## Impact Rules

- **Changing DedgeAuth.Client** → rebuild ALL consumer apps (`Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1`)
- **Changing DedgeAuth wwwroot CSS/JS** → rebuild DedgeAuth only; consumers fetch via proxy
- **Changing tenant branding** → update `tenants` table; no rebuild needed
- **Changing deploy templates** → run `IIS-DeployApp\_deploy.ps1` to sync to servers
